# UI conventions

## Brand

- Header: sunset yellow gradient band, volleyball icon, white Orbitron lockup — not the full OG JPG
- Display font: **Orbitron**; body: **Montserrat**
- Page background: `#f5f5f5` + `tiny-grid.png` with light white overlay
- Fonts: self-hosted Montserrat + Orbitron in `public/fonts/` (see `styles.css` `@font-face`)
- Accent / MUI primary: `#f5ba13` with dark contrast text `#1a1a1a` (never white on yellow)
- CSS tokens in `styles.css`: `--brand-yellow`, `--brand-yellow-soft`, `--brand-sand`, `--shadow-warm`

Extend this look; do not replace with a new design system unless asked.

## Components

- Prefer MUI v5 primitives already used (`Stack`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Divider`, etc.)
- Match siblings: `GameCard`, `PlayerInputField`, `ResultCard`, `Header`, `Footer`, `SimpleBottomNavigation`
- Keep score entry editable after submit; preserve sticky per-game state in `GameCard`

## Layout / UX

- Mobile-first: bottom nav show/hide, sticky score flow, readable forms on small screens
- Alerts via existing snackbar patterns (`SnackbarAlert`)
- Results download uses `html-to-image` with time-based filenames — preserve that behavior when touching export UI
